National fine art show 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 5 (KCNA) -- A national fine art show began at the People's Palace of Culture on October 3 to mark the 4th anniversary of leader Kim Jong Il's election as General Secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea and the 56th anniversary of the WPK.
 On display are 40 fine art works including Korean paintings, oil paintings and posters.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The exhibits fully depict the undying feats and greatness of President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il who wisely led the WPK to a certain victory. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They also show the Korean people pushing ahead with the grand march for socialism under the red flag under the guidance of the party and their revolutionary and optimistic life.

Japan's projected overseas military operation under fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 5 (KCNA) -- Japan's ground, maritime and air "Self-Defence Forces" (SDF) are going to stage joint exercises overseas for the first time in the post-war period. In this regard Rodong Sinmun today in a signed commentary terms it an unpardonable criminal act.
 The commentary goes on:
 The objective of the SDF's projected military exercises in the Indian Ocean and Pakistan is to set a precedent for the simultaneous overseas advance and comprehensive military exercise of the three services of the "SDF" and show that Japan is fully capable of staging any military operation overseas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan's moves to stage such joint military exercises, not bound to legal restrictions and departing from precedent, cannot be construed otherwise than a very dangerous development. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is a clear indication that the Japanese reactionaries have not given up their old dream of "Greater East Asia Co-Prosperity Sphere" though half a century has passed since their defeat and the world greeted a new century but have become more undisguised in their moves to realize their wild ambition for overseas expansion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The crimes committed by Japan in the past are still fresh in the memory of the world people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In view of both their nature and temper, the Japanese militarists represent a war force which can launch aggression any time under any brigandish pretext. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The projected joint military exercises of the "SDF" overseas can never be justified nor can their criminal and dangerous nature be covered up.

Famous writer 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 5 (KCNA) -- New song "Arirang for Prosperity" is popular in the DPRK.
 The song of folk song melody deals with the Korean people creating things on their own efforts and glorifying the dignity of the homeland of the sun with the might of single-hearted unity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The words of the song were written by Yun Tu Gun, 54, creator of the song and dance ensemble of the Korean People's Army. He is a Kim Il Sung Prize winner. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He has created more than 200 famous words of songs and poems since he was a soldier. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 His words of "Song I learned for the first time" won the national musical contest held in 1968 on the occasion of the 20th anniversary of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He wrote nearly 40 songs and poems in his soldier days. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 among them words of "soldiers present arms" and "we learn revolutionary history of leader" respectively placed first and second in the literary work contest of the KPA. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He became a writer of the song and dance ensemble of the KPA in Juche 60 (1971). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 His first work as a writer "Leader, The Night Is Far Advanced" received a special prize in the national literary work contest held in 1975 on the occasion of the 30th anniversary of the Workers' Party of Korea. The song has gripped the hearts of the people across the country and the world progressives as it reflects the unanimous wishes of the Korean people for the good health of President Kim Il Sung who works heart and soul till late at night without having a moment's rest. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then he produced works portraying the leader and reflecting the spirit of the times such as "We will always live with the leader" and "Flower in full bloom all over the country." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Several pieces of words of songs "We believe in you as in heaven," "With same spirit as displayed in 'arduous march'," and "We will never forget," created by Yun In recent years, caused a great sensation in the literature and art circle as they fully reflected the spirit of the times and all the people's thought and feelings.

Minju Joson marks world day of teachers 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 5 (KCNA) -- Diverse functions are being held in different countries to improve education and boost the status of teachers in society and public concern for them on the occasion of the world day of teachers (October 5). 
 On this day Minju Joson today in a signed article says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Korean teachers are devoting all their wisdom and enthusiasm to the education of posterity with the self-conceit and pride of bringing up the reserves of revolution under the best socialist educational system in the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 State concern and favor for teachers are systematically growing in Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The enhanced status and role of teachers in society wrought a signal success in education. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Education is a far-sighted work for the future of humankind and teachers are its undertakers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 UNESCO efforts to enhance the status and role of teachers and contribute to the intellectual development of humankind will bear a good fruition.
